		<technology>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="zh">The metal aluminum in secondary aluminum dross (SAD) can be recovered until 1 wt % is left through grinding and sieving. Chlorides in the solution were recovered through concentration and crystallization. Calcium chloride was used to remove fluoride. Ammonia was absorbed by sulfuric acid and used to produce ammonium sulfate. Ball milling was used to promote the direct reaction between active aluminum components and water. Therefore, the ball milling scenario avoided the use of acid or alkali and achieved the deactivation of SAD, except for the use of sulfuric acid to absorb the ammonia generated during the ball milling process. Alumina and other metal oxide (mainly basic oxide) remained in the dross, making the composition and content close to bauxite-like. Therefore, all remaining dross were reused as bauxite-like in the aluminum industry, without any solid waste generated in the ball milling scenario. In this scenario, the deactivation effect of the active aluminum component was about 95%.</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="en">This industrial process is designed for the treatment and reuse of secondary aluminum dross (SAD) in the aluminum industry. The process involves the recovery of metallic aluminum and the deactivation of active aluminum components in SAD through ball milling, which promotes the direct reaction between active aluminum components and water. The resulting product has a bauxite-like composition and can be reused as an alternative raw material in the aluminum production process, effectively recirculating valuable resources and reducing waste.</technologicalApplicability>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="zh">该工业过程旨在铝行业中二次铝渣（SAD）的处理和再利用。该过程涉及通过球磨工艺从SAD中回收金属铝并失活活性铝成分，球磨促进活性铝成分与水的直接反应。生成的产品具有类似铝土矿的成分，可以用作铝生产过程中的替代原材料，有效循环利用宝贵资源并减少废物。</technologicalApplicability>
			<referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture type="source data set" refObjectId="5827f09a-0c8a-4e99-9559-35e14f54f9ce" uri="../sources/5827f09a-0c8a-4e99-9559-35e14f54f9ce.xml">
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="en">WEnkbd36YoHO4jxTQ69csP3anWc.png</common:shortDescription>
			</referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture>
		</technology>
