			<useAdviceForDataSet xml:lang="en">When utilizing the life cycle assessment data of this process, users must adhere to specific methodological guidelines, including: 1) Apply cut-off rules to focus only on the SAD recovery impacts within the aluminum life cycle; 2) Set system boundaries with a cradle-to-grave perspective that concentrates on the SAD recovery, omitting the environmental impact of transportation; 3) Ensure the correct application of material balance calculations for accurate inventory data, considering the use of coal-based electricity, consistent with China's aluminum industry practices.</useAdviceForDataSet>
			<useAdviceForDataSet xml:lang="zh">当使用该过程的生命周期评估数据时，用户必须遵守特定的方法论指导原则，包括：1) 应用截止规则，仅关注铝生命周期内SAD回收的影响；2) 设置系统边界，采用从摇篮到坟墓的观点，专注于SAD的回收，忽略运输的环境影响；3) 确保正确应用物质平衡计算，以获得准确的清单数据，同时考虑使用符合中国铝工业实际情况的以煤为基础的电力。</useAdviceForDataSet>
		</dataSourcesTreatmentAndRepresentativeness>
		<completeness>
			<common:other xml:lang="en">1) Cut-off rules; 2) System boundaries are set by applying a cut-off system model based on &quot;cradle-to-grave&quot; thinking, which only focuses on the impact of SAD recycling on the entire life cycle of aluminum, including raw material production and waste disposal; 3) Transportation is not included.</common:other>
			<common:other xml:lang="zh">1) 截止规则；2) 系统边界是通过应用基于 &quot;从摇篮到坟墓 &quot;思维的截止系统模型来设定的，该模型只关注 SAD 回收在铝的整个生命周期中的影响，包括原材料生产和废物处置；3) 不包括运输。</common:other>
		</completeness>
